OOP (Classes & Objects) 

OOP = Object Oriented Programming
It helps you organize code using classes and objects.

1. Create a Class
class Student:
    name = "Sanjana"

Student is a class

2. Create Object
class Student:
    name = "Sanjana"

s1 = Student()
print(s1.name)
Output
Sanjana

3. Using __init__ (Constructor)
class Student:
    def __init__(self, name, age):
        self.name = name
        self.age = age

s1 = Student("Sanjana", 20)

print(s1.name)
print(s1.age)
Output
Sanjana
20

4. Method in Class
class Student:
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name

    def greet(self):
        print("Hello", self.name)

s1 = Student("Sanjana")
s1.greet()
Output
Hello Sanjana

5. Class with Multiple Objects
class Student:
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name

s1 = Student("A")
s2 = Student("B")

print(s1.name)
print(s2.name)
Output
A
B

6. Simple Program (Bank Account)
class Bank:
    def __init__(self, balance):
        self.balance = balance

    def deposit(self, amount):
        self.balance += amount
        print("Balance:", self.balance)

b1 = Bank(1000)
b1.deposit(500)
Output
Balance: 1500

7. Access and Modify Object Data
class Student:
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name

s1 = Student("Sanjana")
s1.name = "Anu"

print(s1.name)
Output
Anu
